        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUARTZ on a DWS:</span> At 24 base points, a Double Word Score gives you 48 points. Uses common tiles (U, A, R, T) alongside Q and Z — achievable with the right board position.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QI is your insurance policy:</span> QI (11pts) is the most important Q-word to know. It's 2 letters, needs no U, and scores 11 points minimum. On a TLS, the Q alone contributes 30 points. Always your fallback.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold Q with good company:</span> If you have Q + U + Z or Q + U + K + Y, you're looking at 22-40 point plays. Hold for 1-2 turns. If nothing materializes, dump Q via QI before it costs you the game.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
